
[1]fastness

   F'ASTNESS, n.

   1. The state of being fast and firm; firm adherence.

   2. Strength; security.

   The places of fastness are laid open.

   3. A strong hold; a fortress or fort; a place fortified; a castle. The
   enemy retired to their fastnesses.

   4. Closeness; conciseness of style. [Not used.]
